        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Freshwater</placeName>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>The above address will explain my delay in acknowledging &amp; thanking you for your kind note.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I return home in two days’ time &amp; no doubt shall then find the pamphlet which your distinguished countryman, the Count Mariani (?) has given me the honor of sending.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Should you have any opportunity, I hope that you will present with much respect my thanks to the Count. If on my return home, I do <hi rend="underline">not</hi> find the pamphlet I will communicate with you.</p>
<p>With my best respects and thanks, I remain […]</p>
<p>Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the address. The Darwins stayed at Freshwater on the Isle of Wight from 17 July to 20 August 1868 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)). The addressee, address, and date are provided in the sale catalogue.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Susanni’s letter has not been found in the Darwin Archive–CUL.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6272.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Terenzio Mamiani della Rovere</ref> (see also <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 14, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5059.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Rudolf Suchsland, 16 April 1866</ref> and n. 6). There is a copy of Mamiani’s 1868 article, ‘Nuove considerazione intorno al sistema di Darwin’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5181.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Mamiani della Rovere 1868</ref>) in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL. It is lightly annotated, but not by CD.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The original letter is complete, and according to the sale catalogue is two pages long.</note>
        </div>        
            
